    • Constructor Detail

      • ProjectInformation

        public ProjectInformation(int timeout,
                          SourceCodeFileProvider fileProvider,
                          String buildPath,
                          Charset charset,
                          Set<LaunchConfiguration> launchConfigurations)
        Creates a new Project Information.
        Parameters:
        timeout - The timeout to be used.
        timeout value description
        BeagleConfiguration.ADAPTIVE_TIMEOUTBeagle will use a timeout that adapts to the quality of the analysis’ findings in the past.
        BeagleConfiguration.NO_TIMEOUTno timeout will be used
        ≥ 0the given value will be used as a fixed timeout in seconds
        fileProvider - The provider of the source files to be analysed.
        buildPath - The class path containing everything needed to compile the project.
        charset - The charset used for all files in the project. May be null, in this case Charset.defaultCharset() will be used.
        launchConfigurations - The configurations defining how to launch the measured software. Must not be null, must not contain null, must not be empty.

      • getTimeout

        public int getTimeout()
        Returns the timeout to be used. The timeout describes the minimum time Beagle shall keep trying to find results while no perfect results were found.
        timeout value description
        BeagleConfiguration.ADAPTIVE_TIMEOUTBeagle will use a timeout that adapts to the quality of the analysis’ findings in the past.
        BeagleConfiguration.NO_TIMEOUTno timeout will be used
        ≥ 0the given value will be used as a fixed timeout in seconds
        Returns:
        The timeout that will be used by Beagle.

        public Set<LaunchConfiguration> getLaunchConfigurations()
        Queries the configurations defining how to launch the measured software.
        Returns:
        The project’s launch configurations. Will neither be null, nor contain null, nor be empty.
